articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The source said the handovers would take place under Egyptian supervision but did not specify the release date.
articles.title: Mediators agree swap of Palestinian prisoners for Israeli hostages' bodies, source says

articles.author: James Oliphant
articles.description: Elon Musk, the billionaire adviser tasked with radically downsizing the U.S. government, will attend President Donald Trump's first cabinet meeting on Wednesday as turmoil continues to swirl around his plans to fire federal workers.
articles.title: Musk to attend Trump cabinet meet as workers brace for more uncertainty

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's military has set up a drill zone for "shooting training" about 40 nautical miles (74 km) off Taiwan's southwest coast without prior notification, the island's defence ministry said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Taiwan flags China's 'shooting' drills off  southwest coast

articles.author: Dmitry Antonov, Andrew Osborn
articles.description: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Wednesday that Moscow could not consider "any options" for European peacekeepers being sent to Ukraine and that the idea was aimed at fuelling the conflict and making it harder to de-escalate.
articles.title: Russia rules out 'any options' for European peacekeepers in Ukraine

articles.author: Steve Holland, Kanishka Singh
articles.description: Trump told reporters he will replace the "EB-5" immigrant investor visa program, which allows foreign investors of large sums of money that create or preserve U.S. jobs to become permanent residents, with a so-called "gold card."
articles.title: Trump floats $5 million 'gold card' as a route to US citizenship

articles.author: Brendan Pierson
articles.description: President Donald Trump's administration said in a court filing late Tuesday night that it "cannot" meet a federal judge's 11:59 p.m. Wednesday deadline for releasing frozen funds to foreign aid contractors and grant recipients, potentially setting the stage for it to disobey a court order.
articles.title: Trump administration says it cannot meet court deadline for foreign aid payments

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: President Vladimir Putin hosted Guinea-Bissau President Umaro Sissoco Embalo for talks in the Kremlin on Wednesday, the latest sign of a drive by Moscow to build up economic and security relationships with countries in west and central Africa.
articles.title: Putin hosts Guinea-Bissau leader as Russia builds Africa ties

articles.author: Andy Bruce
articles.description: British finance minister Rachel Reeves said on Wednesday she was confident that U.S.-UK trade and investment would not be derailed as President Donald Trump threatens to retaliate against what he sees as barriers to U.S. exports.
articles.title: UK's Reeves says trade with US can flow amid Trump trade threats
